column157: Out of the 4 interactions I was supposed to have, only 1 worked both with audio and image. On another, both the image worked but the audio did not. On the other two, neither the audio or visual worked; it was a white screen for 4 minutes.
column159: On the 1 interaction that worked (audio and visual both worked, on the other 3 interactions it did not), the video set-up did not impact our conversation other than the limited time we had to talk. On the one call where I could see the other participant, but not hear them, every aspect of our interaction was impacted.
column160: At first, I thought it was to study on first impressions, and how people who have just met and have a limited time to speak interact. But now I am more inclined to think that the study wanted my reactions to poor video/audio quality and overall service.
column162: I only had one successful conversation. From her reactions, I don't think my image was being manipulated. Her responses to me seemed natural and genuine.
